Included in this number are fourteen people who were apprehended in George. CAPE TOWN - Western Cape traffic officials have arrested 35 people for drinking and driving over the weekend. Included in this number are fourteen people who were apprehended in George. Provincial Traffic Chief Kenny Africa said: “Early this morning shortly after 7 pm three truck drivers were arrested outside Laingsburg for driving a vehicle under the influence of alcohol.” (Edited by Thapelo Lekabe)